---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import Link from "../components/Link.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import thumbsup from "../assets/images/thumbsup.png";
import Heading from "../components/Heading.astro";
import Text from "../components/Text.astro";
import Button from "../components/Button.astro";
import LinkCard from "../components/LinkCard.astro";
import Polaroid1 from "../assets/images/Polarid1.webp";
import Polaroid2 from "../assets/images/Polarid2.webp";
import Polaroid3 from "../assets/images/Polarid3.webp";
import pil from "../assets/images/pil.webp";
import pic1 from "../assets/images/pic1.webp";
import pic2 from "../assets/images/pic2.webp";
import pic3 from "../assets/images/pic3.webp";
import Instantdaypic from "../assets/images/Instantdaypic.webp";
import datavisualisering from "../assets/images/datavisualisering.webp";
import Heropic from "../assets/images/Heropic.webp";
---

<script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
<style>
  @keyframes topCycle {
    0%,
    30% {
      z-index: 3;
    }

    33%,
    60% {
      z-index: 2;
    }
    65%,
    100% {
      z-index: 1;
    }
  }
  .animate-top-1 {
    animation: topCycle 9s infinite;
  }
  .animate-top-2 {
    animation: topCycle 9s infinite 3s;
  }
  .animate-top-3 {
    animation: topCycle 9s infinite 6s;
  }
</style>

<MainLayout title="Home">
  <main class="">
    <section class="items-center mb-20 bg-black">
      <Image class="mx-auto" src={Heropic} alt="Foto" />
      <!-- Overskrift med linjeskift kun på mobil -->

      <div class="px-6 sm:px-10 md:px-16 lg:px-24 mt-10">
        <!-- Container for h1 og h2 med afstand -->
        <div class="flex flex-col space-y-8 sm:space-y-10 md:space-y-12">
          <Heading
            htmlheading="h1"
            size="large"
            font="overskrift"
            stylingclasses="md:mb-8 mb-5"
            class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl"
          >
            October 18 is <br class="sm:hidden" />
            Instant Day
          </Heading>
        </div>

        <Button href="#submissionForm">Save the date!</Button>
      </div>

      <!-- What is Instant Day -->
      <section
        class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center gap-12 mb-20"
      >
        {/* Tekstblok – bredere */}
        <div class="md:basis-3/5">
          <Heading htmlheading="h2" size="medium" font="underoverskrift">
            What is Instant Day?
          </Heading>

          <Text stylingclasses="mt-4 ml-10 md:ml-20">
            October 18 is Instant Day – a day all about celebrating instant
            photography. Dig out your Polaroid, Instax or whatever, and shoot
            something! Share your best instant photos on social media or enter
            the competition. A nice prize for one lucky instant photographer!
          </Text>
        </div>

        {/* Billedblok – smallere og med luft */}
        <div class="md:basis-2/5 flex justify-center">
          <Image class="mx-auto sm:mx-0" src={Instantdaypic} alt="Foto" />
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Why Instant Photography -->
      <section class="bg-accent-900 px-6 py-12 mb-20">
        <div
          class="max-w-5xl mx-auto grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 md:items-start gap-12"
        >
          <!-- Billede (5/12 på md+). Mobil: efter teksten -->
          <div class="order-2 md:order-1 md:col-span-5 mt-8 md:mt-0">
            <Image
              class="w-72 h-auto md:mx-0 justify-center items-center mx-auto"
              src={pic3}
              alt="Foto"
            />
          </div>

          <!-- Tekst (7/12 på md+). Mobil: før billedet -->
          <div class="order-1 md:order-2 md:col-span-7">
            <Heading htmlheading="h2" size="medium" font="underoverskrift">
              Why Instant Photography?
            </Heading>

            <Text
              stylingclasses="mt-4 text-base md:text-lg leading-7 md:leading-8 space-y-4 ml-10 md:ml-20"
            >
              Instant Photography is a testament to life: It all started back in
              the 1940’s with a 3 year old kid. She wanted to see her fathers
              images right away. The father, Edwin Land, embarked on a mission:
              To invent instant photography. Half a decade later, Edwin Land
              launched Instant photography and established the Polaroid brand.
              Instant photography turned into big business in the 70’s and 80’s,
              until the digital era almost killed the industry. The massive
              amount of time wasted on the small screens have spurred a
              counterreaction: Analogue, off-line experiences have become
              popular again. And instant photography is just that: An analogue,
              life-affirming and tactile photography experience. So let’s
              celebrate life, and make memories:-)
            </Text>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
      <section class="mx-10">
        <Image class="mx-auto mb-40" src={datavisualisering} alt="Foto" />
      </section>

      <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 mb-20">
        <Heading
          class="text-accent-900"
          htmlheading="h2"
          size="medium"
          font="underoverskrift"
        >
          How to participate
        </Heading>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid md:grid-cols-3 md:gap-8 mt-6">
          {/* Liste i venstre side */}
          <div class="space-y-6 col-span-2">
            <li>
              <Text>
                Take a photo of your instant with your smartphone (or scan for
                max quality) – the file should be between 2–10 MB, jpg/jpeg or
                webp format.
              </Text>
            </li>
            <li>
              <Text>
                Upload your photo and credentials via the “share your instants”
                page.</Text
              >
            </li>
            <li>
              <Text>
                Agree to our terms and conditions. The short version:
                Participants must be 18+, portrayed persons must have given
                consent, and you agree your instant can be exhibited and used to
                promote the contest.
              </Text>
            </li>
            <li>
              <Text>
                You can make up to 5 submissions – repeat step 1–3 for each
                submission ;-)</Text
              >
            </li>
          </div>
          {/* Tekst og pil i højre side */}
          <div
            class="flex flex-col items-center md:items-end justify-center text-accent-900 md:mt-50 mt-10"
          >
            <Text class="mb-2">Still need inspiration?</Text>
            <Image src={pil} alt="Arrow" class="w-15 h-auto" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
      <section class="bg-accent-900 py-12 mb-40 overflow-hidden">
        <!-- centreret “scene” til bunken -->
        <div
          class="relative mx-auto max-w-[600px] sm:max-w-[900px] h-[400px] sm:h-[650px]"
        >
          <!-- Øverste kort -->
          <div
            class="absolute left-1/2 top-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 rotate-[6deg] animate-top-1"
          >
            <Image
              class="w-[36rem] sm:w-[40rem] h-auto select-none pointer-events-none"
              src={pic1}
              alt="Foto"
            />
          </div>

          <!-- Midterste kort -->
          <div
            class="absolute left-1/2 top-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 rotate-[10deg] animate-top-2"
          >
            <Image
              class="w-[36rem] sm:w-[40rem] h-auto select-none pointer-events-none"
              src={pic2}
              alt="Foto"
            />
          </div>

          <!-- Nederste kort -->
          <div
            class="absolute left-1/2 top-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 rotate-[-10deg] animate-top-3"
          >
            <Image
              class="w-[36rem] sm:w-[40rem] h-auto select-none pointer-events-none"
              src={pic3}
              alt="Foto"
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="m-10 md:container md:mx-auto">
        <Heading
          class="text-accent-900"
          htmlheading="h2"
          size="medium"
          font="underoverskrift"
        >
          You can also get a lot of inspiration from<br />the art Photography
          scene.
        </Heading><br />

        <br /><div
          class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-10 justify-items-center md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-20"
        >
          <div class="md:place-self-end">
            <LinkCard
              stylingclasses="bg-secondary-900 text-primary-900 md:place-self-end"
              link="https://www.danisaacwallin.com/"
              h3="Dan Isaac Wallin"
              p="...is a swedish art photographer, who uses large format and vintage polaroid cameras for his work. His work hangs in numerous houses as posters."
              psmall="https://www.danisaacwallin.com/"
              stroke="#000000"
            />
          </div>

          <div class="md:place-self-start">
            <LinkCard
              stylingclasses="bg-accent-900"
              link="https://www.kelterphotography.com/"
              h3="Mette Kelter"
              p="... is a danish art photographer, who often experiments with deliberate destruction of the chemical process in instant photos. One of the key words here is unpredictability in the work process, which leads to interesting and unique artworks."
              psmall="https://www.kelterphotography.com/"
              stroke="#FFFFFF"
            />
          </div>

          <div class="md:order-last md:place-self-start">
            <LinkCard
              stylingclasses="bg-secondary-900 text-primary-900"
              link="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maripol"
              h3="Maripol"
              p="... is a french artist/photographer/film producer. Her claim to fame was in the 1980’s, where she photographed famous people with a Polaroid SX-70. Her photographs are still very influential in the fashion industry. "
              psmall="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maripol"
              stroke="#000000"
            />
          </div>

          <div class="md:place-self-end">
            <LinkCard
              stylingclasses="bg-accent-900"
              link="https://www.taschen.com/en/books/photography/40752/the-polaroid-book-45th-ed/"
              h3="The Polaroid collection"
              p="... instant photographs assembled by the Polaroid corporation and featured work from a lot of famous photographers. The collection was split into various parts and put on auction when the Polaroid corporation went into bankruptcy in 2008. Luckily, you can find books with photographs from the collection, for instance The Polaroid Book by Steve Crist and Barbara Hitchcock. "
              psmall="https://www.taschen.com/"
              stroke="#FFFFFF"
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </section>
  </main>
</MainLayout>
